Atiku Abubakar, presidential candidate of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP), says he cannot wait for the 2019 presidential debate. Atiku said this shortly after his running mate took on Vice-President Yemi Osinbajo at the debate organised by the Nigerian Elections Debate Group (NEDG) and the Broadcasting Organisations of Nigeria (BON). The PDP candidate commended Obi for “laying out our vision to get Nigeria working again”. “I watched with pride as @PeterObi laid out our vision to get Nigeria working again. Can’t wait for the presidential debate,” he tweeted.  2019: Atiku kicks-off campaign with ‘People’s Policy Launch' on Monday I'll make difficult decisions to fix Nigeria – Atiku I will not let you down, Atiku tells PDP delegates